{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"creased-carsick-kitty","creation_channel":"cli","description":"Report #8: `rebar explain E2` / `explain plan` resolved docs/*.md against the CONSUMING repo, which has no docs/ tree, so every coaching deep-link was dead. Fix (already drafted in working tree): move the two prose guides under the packaged `rebar._guides`, render explain_criterion from the registry, read explain_guide via importlib.resources. AC: explain_criterion + explain_guide are repo-root independent; tests cover a docs-less install; docs/ copies become thin pointers.","id":"d109-02df-1dfa-4563","parent_id":"29c2-19c0-2b67-47de","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Package author/criteria guides so `rebar explain` works in a consumer install (#8)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784752645655471001,"uuid":"22db5a19-6591-4ba0-b135-3b2c1271cd81"}